      "span_text": "Out-of-pocket health expenditure (OOP) was estimated at 6.8 per cent of household resources and 12.10 per cent of non-food expenditure in 2011-12. Catastrophic OOP payments increasingly lead to impoverishment through sale of valuable assets, running down savings, and borrowing at usurious interest rates from private money lenders [CITATION_2] ."
